Reasoning: The paper deals with the concept of pseudocodewords, which is a topic in coding theory. Specifically, it focuses on the pseudocodeword redundancy of codes, which is related to the minimum pseudoweight and minimum Hamming distance. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper provides bounds on the pseudocodeword redundancy for families of codes based on designs, which could be relevant to the Discrete Structures (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be of interest to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category, as it deals with the complexity of finding the minimum pseudoweight.
